d for any single action in WWII.","number":1},{"header":"He presided over a school desegregation case","body":"Berry v. School District of the City of Benton Harbor began in the 1970s and wound through the federal courts for decades. Hillman took over the case, issued a comprehensive remedial order in 1981 mandating compensatory education, busing adjustments, and faculty diversification — rejecting inter-district mergers as too disruptive.","number":2},{"header":"He co-founded the World Affairs Council of Western","body":"In 1949, just two years after passing the bar, Douglas Hillman co-founded the World Affairs Council of Western Michigan alongside businessman Edgar Orr. Their mission was to heighten global awareness among Americans, with a particular focus on engaging younger generations through lectures and cultural exchange. The Hillman-Orr Award, named jointly for both founders, continues today, honoring regional contributions to international understanding.","number":3}],"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Chief Judge Douglas Woodruff Hillman","first_name":"Douglas","last_name":"Hillman","middle_name":"Woodruff","title":"Chief Judge","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"douglas-hillman-1922"},"X00826":{"id":"X00826","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"tags":[],"sources":[],"birth":{"year":1923,"city":"Grand Rapids","state":"Michigan"},"death":{"year":2013},"gender":"female","number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"HD2502","end_type":"death","end_year":2007,"children_ids":["HD3139","HD2508"],"date_year":1944,"date_month":9,"date_day":13,"location_city":"Grand Rap